
<h1>The Litany for Ordinations</h1>
<p><i>For use at Ordinations as directed.  On Ember Days or other occasions,<br/>if desired, this Litany may be used for the Prayers of the People at the<br/>Eucharist or the Daily Office, or it may be used separately.</i></p>
<p>God the Father,<br/><i>Have mercy on us.</i></p>
<p>God the Son,<br/><i>Have mercy on us.</i></p>
<p>God the Holy Spirit,<br/><i>Have mercy on us.</i></p>
<p>We pray to you, Lord Christ.<br/><i>Lord, hear our prayer.</i></p>
<p>For the holy Church of God, that it may be filled with truth<br/>and love, and be found without fault at the Day of your<br/>Coming,<br/>we pray to you, O Lord.<br/><i>Lord, hear our prayer.</i></p>
<p>For all members of your Church in their vocation and<br/>ministry, that they may serve you in a true and godly life,<br/>we pray to you, O Lord.<br/><i>Lord, hear our prayer.</i></p>
<p>For <b><span class="person">N</span></b>, our Presiding Bishop, and for all bishops, priests, and<br/>deacons, that they may be filled with your love, may hunger<br/>for truth, and may thirst after righteousness,<br/>we pray to you, O Lord.<br/><i>Lord, hear our prayer.</i></p>
    